  "texts": [
    "Firstly, as expected, the performance of the classifiers reduces significantly in the presence of class imbalances.",
    "When a target class is excluded, the resulting F 1 score for that class is zero.",
    "When a class is withheld from the target domain, the metric-informed procedure finds pseudo-labels for the target data by considering all the classes in the source that are most similar.",
    "This process leads to mislabelling of the existing target domain classes, resulting in poor classification performances for some damage locations.",
    "The pseudo-labels assigned for Scenario 2 demonstrate this effect in Figure 10a."
